  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "To configure TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) mail on an iPhone, you'll typically follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Gather Necessary Information\nBefore you begin, you will need:\n- Your TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com)\n- Your password for your TCS email account\n- Incoming and outgoing mail server settings (you may want to check with your IT department for the most up-to-date settings):\n  - **IMAP/POP3 settings** for incoming email\n  - **SMTP settings** for outgoing email\n\n### Step 2: Open Settings on Your iPhone\n1. Go to **Settings** on your iPhone.\n\n### Step 3: Add Email Account\n1. Scroll down and tap **Mail**.\n2. Tap on **Accounts**.\n3. Tap **Add Account**.\n\n### Step 4: Choose Email Provider\n1. Select **Other** since TCS email might not be listed among the popular email service providers.\n\n### Step 5: Enter Account Information\n1. Tap on **Add Mail Account**.\n2. Enter your name, email address, password, and a description (e.g., TCS Mail).\n3. Tap **Next**.\n\n### Step 6: Configure Incoming Mail Server\n1. Choose either **IMAP** or **POP** according to your preference (IMAP is recommended for syncing).\n   - **Incoming Mail Server**:\n     - Host Name: Enter the IMAP/POP server address provided by TCS.\n     - User Name: Your full TCS email address.\n     - Password: Your email password.\n\n### Step 7: Configure Outgoing Mail Server\n1. Under the SMTP section, tap on the server (if it doesn't auto-fill, tap \"Add Server\").\n   - **Outgoing Mail Server**:\n     - Host Name: Enter the SMTP server address provided by TCS.\n     - User Name: Your full TCS email address.\n     - Password: Your email password.\n\n### Step 8: Save Settings\n1. After entering all the information, tap **Next**. Your iPhone will verify the information.\n2. If everything is correct, tap **Save**.\n\n### Step 9: Test Email Setup\n1. Open the Mail app to see if you can send and receive emails.\n\n### Additional Notes:\n- If you encounter issues, double-check the incoming and outgoing server settings.\n- You might need to enable certain security settings (like SSL).\n- Some companies use specific security protocols, so if prompted, consult your IT department for specific instructions or additional configuration settings.\n\n### Troubleshooting:\n- If you're unable to connect, re-check the username and password.\n- Check your internet connection.\n- Ensure the servers are up and configuration settings are correct.\n- If using two-factor authentication, you may need an app-specific password.\n\nFor the most accurate instructions, it\u2019s always best to refer to your company\u2019s IT support or documentation.",
